---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import SocialLinks from '../components/SocialLinks.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About - Griffin Chure">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="page-header">
      <h1 class="mono-upper">Griffin Chure, PhD</h1>
      <!-- <div class="header-line"></div> -->
    </header>

    <div class="content-wrapper">
      
      <div class="profile-section">
        <img src="/images/headshot-stintson.png" alt="Griffin Chure" class="about-image" />
        <div class="profile-right">
          <div class="social-links-wrapper">
            <SocialLinks size="small" />
          </div>
          <div class="experience-section">
            <h2 class="experience-header mono-upper">Experience</h2>
            <div class="experience-list">
              <div class="experience-item">
                <span class="experience-years">2024&ndash;</span>
                <div class="experience-details">
                  <span class="experience-role">Senior Computational Research Scientist</span>
                  <span class="experience-place">Profluent Bio</span>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="experience-item">
                <span class="experience-years">2021&ndash;2024</span>
                <div class="experience-details">
                  <span class="experience-role">NSF Postdoctoral Research Fellow</span>
                  <span class="experience-place">Stanford University, Dept. of Biology, Jonas Cremer Group</span>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="experience-item">
                <span class="experience-years">2013&ndash;2020</span>
                <div class="experience-details">
                  <span class="experience-role">PhD, Biochemistry & Molecular Biophysics</span>
                  <span class="experience-place">Caltech, Div. of Biology & Biological Engineering,<br/>  Rob Phillips Group</span>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="experience-item">
                <span class="experience-years">2011&ndash;2015</span>
                <div class="experience-details">
                  <span class="experience-role">BS Biology & BS Chemistry</span>
                  <span class="experience-place">University of Utah</span>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p>The short version is that I'm an anti-disciplinary scientist. The
      slightly longer version is that I'm a computational researcher at <a href="https://profluent.bio">Profluent Bio</a> who uses a 
      blend of statistical inference, mathematical modeling, machine learning, and scientific 
      software engineering to better understand the complex behavor of biological systems. 
       </p>

      <p>I am the progeny of two paleontologists and grew up in rural Utah, which 
      was a unique experience. I spent my weekends helping my parents dig up dinosaur
      bones and my spent my weekdays in the local public education system where I was taught that evolution was a
      hoax and dinosaur bones were buried by either the devil or the government (or
      both). Contending with these opposed views of reality strongly influenced how
      I want to understand the world: through the cold, objective, logical lens of math.</p>

      <p>I studied biology and chemistry at the University of Utah, then earned a
      <a href="https://gchure.github.io/phd">PhD in Biochemistry and Molecular Biophysics</a>
      with <a href="https://rpgroup.caltech.edu">Rob Phillips</a> at Caltech, where I
      learned to approach biological problems from a physical and probabilistic
      perspective. I continued as an NSF Postdoctoral Fellow with
      <a href="https://cremerlab.github.io">Jonas Cremer</a> at Stanford, studying
      the intersection of molecular biophysics, bacterial physiology, and evolution.
      I am now  a senior computational research scientist at
      <a href="https://profluent.bio">Profluent Bio</a> where I use bioinformatics
      and protein language modeling to discover and design protein systems for
      genetic engineering.</p>

      <p>Outside of work hours, I build and maintain scientific resources like the
      <a href="https://anthroponumbers.org">Human Impacts Database</a> and
      <a href="https://cremerlab.github.io/hplc-py">hplc-py</a>. Beyond science, I love
      taking photographs, making vector illustrations, and exploring the wildlands of California with my
      partner and our two hounds. I watch my fair share of films about which I have
      hard-headed opinions such as affinity for Alejandro Jodorowsky and Julia Ducournau,
      a distaste for Star Wars and Marvel.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .content-wrapper {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.7;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .profile-section {
    float: left;
    margin: 0 2rem 2rem 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    shape-outside: margin-box;
  }

  .about-image {
    width: 280px;
    height: auto;
    border-radius: 6px;
    border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
  }

  .profile-right {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .social-links-wrapper {
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .content-wrapper p {
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    text-align: justify;
  }

  .content-wrapper p:first-of-type {
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .experience-section {
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    width: 100%;
  }

  .experience-header {
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--text-tertiary);
    letter-spacing: 0.03em;
  }

  .experience-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.6rem;
  }

  .experience-item {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0;
  }

  .experience-years {
    font-family: 'Geist Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.65rem;
    color: var(--text-tertiary);
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
  }

  .experience-details {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0;
  }

  .experience-role {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    line-height: 1.3;
  }

  .experience-place {
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .profile-section {
      float: none;
      margin: 0 0 2rem 0;
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1.5fr;
      gap: 1.25rem;
      align-items: start;
      width: 100%;
    }

    .about-image {
      width: 100%;
      max-width: none;
    }

    .profile-right {
      align-items: flex-start;
    }

    .social-links-wrapper {
      margin-top: 0;
    }

    .experience-section {
      margin-top: 0.75rem;
    }

    .experience-header {
      font-size: 0.6rem;
      margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }

    .experience-list {
      gap: 0.4rem;
    }

    .experience-years {
      font-size: 0.55rem;
    }

    .experience-role {
      font-size: 0.65rem;
    }

    .experience-place {
      font-size: 0.6rem;
    }

    .content-wrapper p {
      text-align: left;
    }
  }
</style>
